---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import TracePlayer from "../../islands/TracePlayer.svelte";
import LessonNav from "../../components/LessonNav.astro";
import Term from "../../components/Term.astro";
import buggy from "../../../derived/ifelse/buggy.trace.json";
import procedural from "../../../derived/ifelse/procedural.trace.json";

// Buggy first: watch it fail in real state, then watch the fix.
const registers = [buggy, procedural];
---

<Base title="if / else — GlassBox" description="Two separate ifs both run; the second clobbers the first. elif/else makes exactly one win.">
  <LessonNav slug="ifelse" position="top" />

  <h1>Choosing one branch with if / else</h1>
  <p class="lede">Two back-to-back <code>if</code> statements are two independent decisions — both can run. When you meant 'do one or the other', that's a bug, and the last <Term s="branch">branch</Term> silently wins. Watch <code>grade</code> get set, then overwritten.</p>

  <TracePlayer registers={registers} client:visible />

  <section class="explain card">
    <h2>What you are looking at</h2>
    <p>Watch <code>grade</code>: it's set once, then changed again.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Buggy</strong> — Both <code>if</code>s test true for 85, so <code>grade</code> becomes <code>'distinction'</code> and is then overwritten by <code>'pass'</code>. Two separate ifs, both fired.</li>
      <li><strong>Procedural</strong> — Joining them with <code>elif</code> makes them one decision — the moment the first matches, the rest are skipped, so <code>grade</code> stays <code>'distinction'</code>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="fineprint">Every state you see came from running the program under CPython's tracer at build time — see <a href="../../verification/">how GlassBox stays honest</a>.</p>
  </section>
  <LessonNav slug="ifelse" position="bottom" />
</Base>

<style>
  .explain { margin-top: 1.4rem; }
  .explain ul { margin: 0.6rem 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; }
  .explain li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  .fineprint { color: var(--ink-faint); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0; }
</style>
